des:
Mus Flame app help you control home appliance.You can simply ask Alexa to turn on or turn off your fireplace.
There’s no need to go to the switch to adjust your firepalce - just talk to Alexa on your Amazon Echo.
After connecting Alexa to your fireplace in a few simple steps:
(1). Download our "Mus Flame" app in android or ios app market;
(2). Register an account in our "Mus Flame" app;
(3). You need to have some Mus Flame devices in hand;
(4). Configure these devices in our "Mus Flame" app and change appropriate name for your devices which will be used in "Mus Flame" skills;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from android,ios or Amazon app market;
(6). Configure Echo with "Alexa" app;
(7). Search "Mus Flame" skill from the "Alexa" app skills category;
(8). Click Enable skill of "Mus Flame", and you'll be navigated to "Mus Flame" login page;
(9). Input your Mus Flame account username and password, you'll be redirect to the success page;
(10). Now all setup is finished.
You can enjoy the voice control on your home devices like these:
“Alexa, turn on the bedroom fireplace.”
“Alexa, turn off the bedroom fireplace.”
“Alexa, turn on flame on the fireplace.”
“Alexa, turn off flame on the fireplace.”
“Alexa, set fireplace to auto mode.”
“Alexa, set fireplace to 25 degrees.”
“Alexa, what's the temperature in here? ”
